*** GAMS/KNITRO option file for ReEDS
*** Docs: https://www.gams.com/latest/docs/S_KNITRO.html
***       https://www.artelys.com/app/docs/knitro/3_referenceManual/userOptions.html
*** Activate with: model.OptFile = 1;
***
*** IMPORTANT: Knitro is primarily an NLP/MINLP solver, but it does include
*** dedicated LP and QP solvers that can call CPLEX or Xpress as the underlying
*** LP engine. For pure LP testing on ReEDS:
***   - Cleanest: have Knitro recognize ReEDS as an LP and call the bundled
***     LP solver via act_lpsolver and act_lpalg.
***   - To submit ReEDS to Knitro from GAMS, you typically need to allow NLP:
***       option NLP = KNITRO;
***       solve ReEDSmodel using NLP minimizing Z_obj;
*** Knitro will detect linearity and dispatch the LP solver.

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Algorithm selection
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** algorithm: 0 auto (recommended), 1 Interior/Direct, 2 Interior/CG,
***            3 Active Set, 4 SQP, 5 Multi-algorithm
***
*** For an LP, Knitro's auto picker will choose the LP path; an explicit choice
*** of 1 (Interior/Direct) also resolves to LP barrier internally on LP input.
algorithm 0

*** LP-subproblem algorithm when Active Set / SQP is used.
*** 0 default, 1 primal simplex, 2 dual simplex, 3 barrier
act_lpalg 3

*** LP solver used by Knitro for LP problems / LP subproblems.
*** 1 = internal Knitro LP, 2 = CPLEX (recommended for ReEDS-scale), 3 = Xpress
act_lpsolver 1

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Parallelism
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Total threads (matches the CPLEX baseline)
numthreads 8

*** Linear-algebra threads (for the underlying KKT solves in interior-point)
blas_numthreads 8
linsolver_numthreads 8

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Linear system / inertia handling
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** linsolver: 0 auto, 1 internal, 2 hybrid, 3 dense QR, 4 MA27, 5 MA57,
***            6 MKL Pardiso, 7 MA97, 8 SPRAL
*** MA57 is a good default on Linux for ReEDS-scale problems if HSL is licensed.
linsolver 5

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Convergence tolerances - matched to ReEDS cplex.opt
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Relative feasibility tolerance (CPLEX eprhs 1e-5)
feastol 1e-5
feastol_abs 1e-5

*** Relative optimality tolerance (CPLEX epopt 1e-6)
opttol 1e-6
opttol_abs 1e-6

*** Stop on tiny feasible changes in the objective
ftol 1e-12
ftol_iters 5

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Iteration / time limits
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Wall-clock limit in seconds (2 days, matches cplex.opt reslim)
maxtime_real 172800

*** Maximum major iterations
maxit 10000

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Presolve / scaling
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** presolve: -1 auto, 0 off, 1 on
presolve 1

*** scale: 0 no scaling, 1 user, 2 internal scaling (default), 3 dynamic
scale 2

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Barrier-specific knobs
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** bar_maxcrossit: 0 = no crossover after IPM (default - faster but no basic solution)
***                 positive = at most that many crossover iterations to an Active-Set
***                 solution. ReEDS uses marginals downstream, so request crossover.
bar_maxcrossit 5

*** Initial barrier parameter mu - "auto" lets Knitro choose
bar_initmu -1

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Output
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** outlev: 0 quiet, 1 summary, 2 iteration, 3 detailed, 4-6 debug
outlev 4

*** Print frequency for iteration log
outmode 1

threads = 8